subject: Swimming
lead_paragraph: The Olympic champion Aaron Peirsol held off Michael Phelps in the 200 backstroke in 1 minute 55.81 seconds to win at the Santa Clara (Calif.) Grand Prix. Phelps, who has never beaten Peirsol in the backstroke, was second in 1:55.84. Peirsol’s time was the fastest in the world this year.
